Sentencas: The cubic fluorite structure Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) film was fabricated by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) to be used as electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 film for SOFC electrolyte fabricated by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The SDC target was prepared by co-precipitation process at a low sintering temperature (1,250 degrees C) with a relative density of 97 %.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 film for SOFC electrolyte fabricated by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: By inserting the PLD seed layer with the thickness of 3 mu m, robust electrolyte films were successfully fabricated on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) substrate.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 film for SOFC electrolyte fabricated by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The SDC film growing at a substrate temperature of 650 degrees C with thermal treatment and oxygen gas pressure of 10 Pa has high ionic conductivity of 0.075 S center dot cm(-1) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 film for SOFC electrolyte fabricated by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that the dense SDC thin films prepared by PLD are suitable for low-temperature SOFC applications.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical properties of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 film for SOFC electrolyte fabricated by pulsed laser deposition
